This present-day country was home to the Mossi Kingdoms prior to French colonization. The Agacher Strip War was fought between this country and its northern neighbor over a border dispute. During a 2014 uprising in this country, its president Blaise Compaoré was pressured to resign. Another president of this country seized power from Jean-Baptiste Ouédraogo and planted millions of trees.

This present-day country was home to the Mossi Kingdoms prior to French colonization. The Agacher Strip War was fought between this country and its northern neighbor over a border dispute. During a 2014 uprising in this country, its president Blaise Compaoré was pressured to resign. Another president of this country seized power from Jean-Baptiste Ouédraogo and planted millions of trees. That president, Thomas Sankara, renamed the country from Upper Volta to its present name. For ten points, name this West African country whose capital is Ouagadougou.
